Glean Customer Event logs are written by default to a `glean-customer-event` stream in object storage within your Glean project.

For the latest export and schema documentation, see:
- https://docs.glean.com/administration/gce-logs/data-dictionary
- https://docs.glean.com/administration/gce-logs/data-dictionary-detailed

**Setup steps:**

1. Confirm where your GCE logs are delivered (GCS bucket, S3 bucket, or Firehose stream). Contact your Glean account team if unsure.
2. Configure your export pipeline to write NDJSON objects into this proxy instance's `-input` bucket (any object key path is supported).
3. Gzip files and set `Content-Encoding: gzip` on upload for best performance.
4. Sanitized files appear in the `-sanitized` bucket with the same object keys.
